The published image bundles third-party software. Most components are installed
UNMODIFIED from the Debian 12 (bookworm) archive; for those the corresponding
source is available from Debian's published sources for the matching package
versions. cdrdao and its gcdmaster GUI are instead built UNMODIFIED from the
upstream Git repository at a pinned commit (see component 2), because Debian no
longer packages the gcdmaster GUI. Each component keeps its own license.


Bundled components
------------------

1. jlesage/baseimage-gui (base image)
   License : MIT
   Source  : https://github.com/jlesage/docker-baseimage-gui
   Provides: TigerVNC, noVNC, NGINX, Openbox, and the container init system.

2. cdrdao + gcdmaster  (disc-at-once CD recording engine and its GTK GUI)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Built   : unmodified from upstream source at the commit pinned in the
             Dockerfile (ARG CDRDAO_REF), prefix /usr/local.
   Source  : https://github.com/cdrdao/cdrdao
   Upstream: https://cdrdao.sourceforge.net/
   Note    : gcdmaster (the GTK front-end) is no longer packaged by Debian, so
             it is compiled from this source rather than installed via apt.

3. cdrkit / wodim  (wodim, optional data-CD backend)
   License : GPL-2.0-only
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/cdrkit

4. dvd+rw-tools  (optional DVD backend)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/dvd+rw-tools

For the K3b sibling image, additionally:

5. k3b  (KDE CD/DVD burning suite, installed from the Debian package)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/k3b
   Upstream: https://apps.kde.org/k3b/


Source availability
-------------------

For cdrdao and gcdmaster (component 2), the complete corresponding source is the
upstream Git repository at the commit pinned in the Dockerfile (ARG CDRDAO_REF):

   git clone https://github.com/cdrdao/cdrdao
   git checkout <CDRDAO_REF from the Dockerfile>

For the Debian-packaged GPL components (wodim, dvd+rw-tools, k3b), fetch the
matching Debian source package, for example:

   apt-get source k3b

run against a Debian 12 (bookworm) apt source list, or browse the Debian source
tracker links listed above. The exact package versions in any given build are
those present in the Debian 12 archive at image build time.
